  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p>The stunning panoramas of the Austrian Alps and the turquoise waters of the Lakes both offer breathtaking scenery and are two of Austria’s biggest draws. Combining one ‘Lakes’ resort with one ‘Mountain’ resort to make the most of your time away is a popular choice and also offers a wider variety of excursions. Or why not combine two pretty Alpine villages with contrasting hiking terrain, or combine a lakes &amp; mountains resort with a few days of sightseeing in Salzburg or Vienna? These are our suggestions for our most popular twin and multi centre combinations which best complement each other.</p>
<div class="data-grid" style="float: center;">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="tablet-button" style="height: 50px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td height="20" align="center" valign="middle" style="background-color: #89aa4d; border-top-left-radius: 4px; border-bottom-left-radius: 4px; border-top-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-right-radius: 4px; background-clip: padding-box; font-size: 18px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; text-align: center; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold; padding-left: 18px; padding-right: 18px;">For more information or to book these popular Twin Centre Holidays, please call 01483 79 11 11</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Kitzbühel &amp; Zell am See</h2>
<p><img src="/media/13054380/kitzbuhel-zas.jpg" alt="Kitzbuhel -zas" rel="878,150" /></p>
<p><br />Our most popular combination of two scenic resorts with lively medieval centres filled with shops, cafés and restaurants, both offering a wide variety of activities and excursions as well as excellent walking. Zell am See is one of Austria’s best loved lakes and mountain resorts, with a beautiful lakeside lido and not far from the iconic Kitzsteinhorn glacier. Transfer is just 45 minutes by train.</p>
<p>Please call our reservation team for prices.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Mayrhofen &amp; Lech</h2>
<p><img src="/media/13054383/mayrhofen-lech.jpg" alt="Mayrhofen -lech" rel="878,150" /></p>
<p><br />A great combination of two contrasting regions and villages - Mayrhofen is a lively bustling village situated in the Ziller valley; mountains where you can enjoy a variety of walking paths across the Zillertal, ranging from gentle trails through meadows to high altitude treks into different valleys. Lech is a true walker’s paradise, nestling high up in the impressive Arlberg mountains where you can enjoy FREE use of all cable cars and walkers’ buses.</p>
<p>Please call our reservation team for prices.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Filzmoos &amp; Fuschl</h2>
<p><img src="/media/13054364/filzmoos-fuschl.jpg" alt="Filzmoos -fuschl" rel="878,150" /></p>
<p><br />Ideal for nature lovers seeking peaceful, picturesque postcard villages surrounded by breathtaking scenery, these tiny villages have two of the most stunning settings in Austria, with scenic lake views and sunsets in Fuschl and open meadows at the foot of the Bischofsmütze in Filzmoos. </p>
<p><span>Please call our reservation team for prices.</span></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Kitzbühel &amp; St Wolfgang</h2>
<p><img src="/media/13054379/kitzbuhel-wolfgang.jpg" alt="Kitzbuhel -wolfgang" rel="878,150" /></p>
<p><br />Two of Austria’s best known and iconic resorts, both with colourful painted buildings, cobbled streets, great café culture and good bases for excursions. Kitzbühel &amp; St Wolfgang stands out for their charming medieval centres and St Wolfgang for its turquoise Lake where you can enjoy a trip on the famous St Josef paddle steamer.</p>
<p><span>Please call our reservation team for prices.</span></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Seefeld &amp; Mayrhofen</h2>
<p><img src="/media/13054400/seefeld-mayrhofen.jpg" alt="Seefeld -mayrhofen" rel="878,150" /></p>
<p><br />Two of Tyrol’s favourite villages, both with lively pedestrian areas lined with cafés and restaurants. Excellent bases for a holiday filled with varied activities, guided walks, cycling and contrasting excursions. Seefeld is a large bustling village on a scenic plateau close to Innsbruck; Mayrhofen is in the beautiful Ziller Valley, where you could take a scenic steam train ride.</p>
<p><strong>14 nights from £1,489</strong></p>
<p>Hotel Seespitz, Seefeld &amp; Hotel Neuhaus, Mayrhofen. Other combinations are available.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Salzburg &amp; Zell am See</h2>
<p><br />Combine sightseeing, music, art and shopping in historic Salzburg with one of Austria’s best loved lakes and mountain resorts. There are magnificent walks accessed by gondola on the Schmittenhole mountain and the resort offers a wide range of activities.</p>
<p><strong>10 nights from £1,279</strong></p>
<p>Hotel Markus Sittikus (B&amp;B), Salzburg &amp; Hotel Berner, Zell am See. Other combinations are available.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Vienna &amp; Zell am See</h2>
<p><br />Cultural Vienna with its medieval lanes, cobblestone squares and famous sights combined with one of the most popular summer resorts located on the shores of Lake Zell, flanked on all sides by stunning mountain ranges.</p>
<p><strong>10 nights from £1,189</strong></p>
<p>Hotel Post, Vienna &amp; Romantikhotel, Zell am See. Other combinations are available.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Lech &amp; La Villa</h2>
<p><br />Experience the contrasting cultures and scenery of the Austrian Alps and the Italian Dolomites. During the summer months, la Villa nestles peacefully at the foot of the mountains and is a popular destination for walking.</p>
<p><strong>14 nights from £1,349</strong></p>
<p>Chalet Hotel Montfort, Lech &amp; Chalet Hotel Al Pigher, La Villa ( offered as a first resort). Other combinations are available.</p>
</div>
